In [2]:
TW2=TracyWidom;
F1=Fun(x->cdf(TW2,x; beta=1,num_points=300),-10..13);
F2=Fun(x->cdf(TW2,x; beta=2,num_points=300),-10..13);
F4=Fun(x->cdf(TW2,x; beta=4,num_points=300),-10..13);
f1=F1';
f2=F2';
f4=F4';

The following algorithm outputs the plot showing how the absolute error over the entire domain $x\in[-10,13]$ changes with respect $\beta=1,2,4$. $\Delta x=-0.01$ and $M=1000$.

In [3]:
function err_cdf(D)
    er_cdf=Plots.plot();
    beta=[1,2,4];
    err1=zeros(length(D),1);
    err2=zeros(length(D),1);
    err4=zeros(length(D),1);
    for j=1:length(beta)
        global =beta[j]
        F_cdf=TW()
        for i=1:length(D)
            temp=D[i]
            if ==4
                err4[i]=abs(F_cdf(temp/(2^(1/6)))-cdf(TW2,temp;beta=4,num_points=300))
            elseif ==1
                err1[i]=abs(F_cdf(temp)-cdf(TW2,temp;beta=1,num_points=300))
            elseif ==2
                err2[i]=abs(F_cdf(temp)-cdf(TW2,temp;beta=2,num_points=300))
            end
        end
        for i=1:length(D)
            if err1[i]<10^(-16)
                err1[i]=10^(-16)
            end
            if err2[i]<10^(-16)
                err2[i]=10^(-16)
            end
            if err4[i]<10^(-16)
                err4[i]=10^(-16)
            end
        end
        if ==1
            er_cdf=Plots.plot!(D,err1,lw=5,label=L"$\beta=1$",yaxis=:log10,xtickfontsize=15,ytickfontsize=15,legendfontsize=10,
                yticks=[10^(-16),10^(-14),10^(-12),10^(-10),10^(-8),10^(-6)],
                xticks=D[end]:2:D[1])
        elseif ==2
            er_cdf=Plots.plot!(D,err2,lw=5,label=L"$\beta=2$",yaxis=:log10,xtickfontsize=15,ytickfontsize=15,legendfontsize=10,
                yticks=[10^(-16),10^(-14),10^(-12),10^(-10),10^(-8),10^(-6)],
                xticks=D[end]:2:D[1])
        elseif ==4
            er_cdf=Plots.plot!(D,err4,lw=5,label=L"$\beta=4$",yaxis=:log10,xtickfontsize=15,ytickfontsize=15,legendfontsize=10,
                yticks=[10^(-16),10^(-14),10^(-12),10^(-10),10^(-8),10^(-6)],
                xticks=D[end]:2:D[1])
        end
    end
    return er_cdf
end

X=-8:2:8;
err=zeros(length(X),3);
B=[1,2,4];
for i=1:length(B)
    global =B[i]
    F_cdf=TW()
    for j=1:length(X)
        temp=X[j]
        if ==4
            err[j,3]=abs(F_cdf(temp/(2^(1/6)))-cdf(TW2,temp;beta=4,num_points=300))
        elseif ==1
            err[j,1]=abs(F_cdf(temp)-cdf(TW2,temp;beta=1,num_points=300))
        elseif ==2
            err[j,2]=abs(F_cdf(temp)-cdf(TW2,temp;beta=2,num_points=300))
        end
    end
end

function err_pdf(D)
    er_pdf=Plots.plot();
    beta=[1,2,4];
    err1=zeros(length(D),1);
    err2=zeros(length(D),1);
    err4=zeros(length(D),1);
    for j=1:length(beta)
        global =beta[j]
        F_pdf=TW(;pdf=true)
        for i=1:length(D)
            temp=D[i]
            if ==4
                err4[i]=abs(F_pdf(temp/(2^(1/6)))*(2^(-1/6))-f4(temp))
            elseif ==1
                err1[i]=abs(F_pdf(temp)-f1(temp))
            elseif ==2
                err2[i]=abs(F_pdf(temp)-f2(temp))
            end
        end
        for i=1:length(D)
            if err1[i]<10^(-16)
                err1[i]=10^(-16)
            end
            if err2[i]<10^(-16)
                err2[i]=10^(-16)
            end
            if err4[i]<10^(-16)
                err4[i]=10^(-16)
            end
        end
        if ==1
            er_pdf=Plots.plot!(D,err1,lw=5,label=L"$\beta=1$",yaxis=:log10,xtickfontsize=15,ytickfontsize=15,legendfontsize=10,
                yticks=[10^(-16),10^(-14),10^(-12),10^(-10),10^(-8),10^(-6),10^(-5)],
                xticks=D[end]:2:D[1])
        elseif ==2
            er_pdf=Plots.plot!(D,err2,lw=5,label=L"$\beta=2$",yaxis=:log10,xtickfontsize=15,ytickfontsize=15,legendfontsize=10,
                yticks=[10^(-16),10^(-14),10^(-12),10^(-10),10^(-8),10^(-6),10^(-5)],
                xticks=D[end]:2:D[1])
        elseif ==4
            er_pdf=Plots.plot!(D,err4,lw=5,label=L"$\beta=4$",yaxis=:log10,xtickfontsize=15,ytickfontsize=15,legendfontsize=10,
                yticks=[10^(-16),10^(-14),10^(-12),10^(-10),10^(-8),10^(-6),10^(-5)],
                xticks=D[end]:2:D[1])
        end
    end
    return er_pdf
end

Error plots with respect to $\left|\Delta x\right|$ and $M$¶


CDF¶

The following algorithm outputs the plot showing how the absolute error over the entire domain $x\in[-10,13]$ changes when $\left|\Delta x\right|$ decreases and $M$ increases for a fixed $\beta$-value.

In [9]:
function err_cdfc(,D)
    er_cdfc=Plots.plot();
    delta_x=[-0.02,-0.01,-0.005,-0.0025,-0.00125];
    for j=1:length(delta_x)
        err=zeros(length(D),1)
        dx=delta_x[j];
        F_cdf=TW(;x_f=dx)
        for i=1:length(D)
            temp=D[i]
            if ==4
                err[i]=abs(F_cdf(temp/(2^(1/6)))-cdf(TW2,temp;beta=4,num_points=300))
            elseif ==1
                err[i]=abs(F_cdf(temp)-cdf(TW2,temp;beta=1,num_points=300))
            elseif ==2
                err[i]=abs(F_cdf(temp)-cdf(TW2,temp;beta=2,num_points=300))
            end
        end
        for i=1:length(D)
            if err[i]<10^(-16)
                err[i]=10^(-16)
            end
        end
        if j==1
            er_cdfc=Plots.plot!(D,err,lw=5,label=L"$\Delta x=-0.02$",yaxis=:log10,xtickfontsize=15,ytickfontsize=15,legendfontsize=10,
                yticks=[10^(-16),10^(-14),10^(-12),10^(-10),10^(-8),10^(-6),10^(-4),10^(-3),10^(-2)],xticks=D[end]:2:D[1])
        elseif j==2
            er_cdfc=Plots.plot!(D,err,lw=5,label=L"$\Delta x=-0.01$",yaxis=:log10,xtickfontsize=15,ytickfontsize=15,legendfontsize=10,
                yticks=[10^(-16),10^(-14),10^(-12),10^(-10),10^(-8),10^(-6),10^(-4),10^(-3),10^(-2)],xticks=D[end]:2:D[1])
        elseif j==3
            er_cdfc=Plots.plot!(D,err,lw=5,label=L"$\Delta x=-0.005$",yaxis=:log10,xtickfontsize=15,ytickfontsize=15,legendfontsize=10,
                yticks=[10^(-16),10^(-14),10^(-12),10^(-10),10^(-8),10^(-6),10^(-4),10^(-3),10^(-2)],xticks=D[end]:2:D[1])
        elseif j==4
            er_cdfc=Plots.plot!(D,err,lw=5,label=L"$\Delta x=-0.0025$",yaxis=:log10,xtickfontsize=15,ytickfontsize=15,legendfontsize=10,
                yticks=[10^(-16),10^(-14),10^(-12),10^(-10),10^(-8),10^(-6),10^(-4),10^(-3),10^(-2)],xticks=D[end]:2:D[1])
        elseif j==5
            er_cdfc=Plots.plot!(D,err,lw=5,label=L"$\Delta x=-0.00125$",yaxis=:log10,xtickfontsize=15,ytickfontsize=15,legendfontsize=10,
                yticks=[10^(-16),10^(-14),10^(-12),10^(-10),10^(-8),10^(-6),10^(-4),10^(-3),10^(-2)],xticks=D[end]:2:D[1])
        end
    end
    return er_cdfc
end

Error plots with respect to $x_{0}$¶


CDF¶

The following plot shows the absolute error after interpolation over the domain $x\in[-10,4]$ with respect to $x_{0}$. $\beta=2$, $x_{0}=14,12,10,8,6,4$.

In [45]:
function err_x0(D)
    er_x0=Plots.plot();
    X=[14,12,10,8,6,4]
    err2=zeros(length(D),1);
    for j=1:length(X)
        global xx=X[j]
        F_cdf=TW(2;x0=xx)
        for i=1:length(D)
            temp=D[i]
            err2[i]=abs(F_cdf(temp)-cdf(TW2,temp;beta=2,num_points=300))
        end
        for i=1:length(D)
            if err2[i]<10^(-16)
                err2[i]=10^(-16)
            end
        end
        if xx==14
            er_x0=Plots.plot!(D,err2,lw=5,label=L"$x_{0}=14$",yaxis=:log10,xtickfontsize=15,ytickfontsize=15,legendfontsize=10,
                yticks=[10^(-16),10^(-14),10^(-12),10^(-10),10^(-8),10^(-6)],
                xticks=D[end]:2:D[1],legend=:topleft)
        elseif xx==12
            er_x0=Plots.plot!(D,err2,lw=5,label=L"$x_{0}=12$",yaxis=:log10,xtickfontsize=15,ytickfontsize=15,legendfontsize=10,
                yticks=[10^(-16),10^(-14),10^(-12),10^(-10),10^(-8),10^(-6)],
                xticks=D[end]:2:D[1],legend=:topleft)
        elseif xx==10
            er_x0=Plots.plot!(D,err2,lw=5,label=L"$x_{0}=10$",yaxis=:log10,xtickfontsize=15,ytickfontsize=15,legendfontsize=10,
                yticks=[10^(-16),10^(-14),10^(-12),10^(-10),10^(-8),10^(-6)],
                xticks=D[end]:2:D[1],legend=:topleft)
        elseif xx==8
            er_x0=Plots.plot!(D,err2,lw=5,label=L"$x_{0}=8$",yaxis=:log10,xtickfontsize=15,ytickfontsize=15,legendfontsize=10,
                yticks=[10^(-16),10^(-14),10^(-12),10^(-10),10^(-8),10^(-6)],
                xticks=D[end]:2:D[1],legend=:topleft)
        elseif xx==6
            er_x0=Plots.plot!(D,err2,lw=5,label=L"$x_{0}=6$",yaxis=:log10,xtickfontsize=15,ytickfontsize=15,legendfontsize=10,
                yticks=[10^(-16),10^(-14),10^(-12),10^(-10),10^(-8),10^(-6)],
                xticks=D[end]:2:D[1],legend=:topleft)
        elseif xx==4
            er_x0=Plots.plot!(D,err2,lw=5,label=L"$x_{0}=4$",yaxis=:log10,xtickfontsize=15,ytickfontsize=15,legendfontsize=10,
                yticks=[10^(-16),10^(-14),10^(-12),10^(-10),10^(-8),10^(-6)],
                xticks=D[end]:2:D[1],legend=:topleft)
        end
    end
    return er_x0
end

The following plot shows the absolute error after interpolation over the domain $x\in[-4,13]$ with respect to $x_{N}$. $\beta=2$, $x_{N}=-14,-12,-10,-8,-6,-4$.

In [72]:
function err_xN(D)
    er_xN=Plots.plot();
    X=[-14,-12,-10,-8,-6,-4]
    err2=zeros(length(D),1);
    for j=1:length(X)
        global xx=X[j]
        F_cdf=TW(2;xN=xx)
        for i=1:length(D)
            temp=D[i]
            err2[i]=abs(F_cdf(temp)-cdf(TW2,temp;beta=2,num_points=300))
        end
        for i=1:length(D)
            if err2[i]<10^(-16)
                err2[i]=10^(-16)
            end
        end
        if xx==-14
            er_xN=Plots.plot!(D,err2,lw=5,label=L"$x_{N}=-14$",yaxis=:log10,xtickfontsize=15,ytickfontsize=15,legendfontsize=10,
                yticks=[10^(-16),10^(-14),10^(-12),10^(-10),10^(-8),10^(-6),10^(-5),10^(-4)],
                xticks=D[end]:2:D[1],legend=:bottomleft)
        elseif xx==-12
            er_xN=Plots.plot!(D,err2,lw=5,label=L"$x_{N}=-12$",yaxis=:log10,xtickfontsize=15,ytickfontsize=15,legendfontsize=10,
                yticks=[10^(-16),10^(-14),10^(-12),10^(-10),10^(-8),10^(-6),10^(-5),10^(-4)],
                xticks=D[end]:2:D[1],legend=:bottomleft)
        elseif xx==-10
            er_xN=Plots.plot!(D,err2,lw=5,label=L"$x_{N}=-10$",yaxis=:log10,xtickfontsize=15,ytickfontsize=15,legendfontsize=10,
                yticks=[10^(-16),10^(-14),10^(-12),10^(-10),10^(-8),10^(-6),10^(-5),10^(-4)],
                xticks=D[end]:2:D[1],legend=:bottomleft)
        elseif xx==-8
            er_xN=Plots.plot!(D,err2,lw=5,label=L"$x_{N}=-8$",yaxis=:log10,xtickfontsize=15,ytickfontsize=15,legendfontsize=10,
                yticks=[10^(-16),10^(-14),10^(-12),10^(-10),10^(-8),10^(-6),10^(-5),10^(-4)],
                xticks=D[end]:2:D[1],legend=:bottomleft)
        elseif xx==-6
            er_xN=Plots.plot!(D,err2,lw=5,label=L"$x_{N}=-6$",yaxis=:log10,xtickfontsize=15,ytickfontsize=15,legendfontsize=10,
                yticks=[10^(-16),10^(-14),10^(-12),10^(-10),10^(-8),10^(-6),10^(-5),10^(-4)],
                xticks=D[end]:2:D[1],legend=:bottomleft)
        elseif xx==-4
            er_xN=Plots.plot!(D,err2,lw=5,label=L"$x_{N}=-4$",yaxis=:log10,xtickfontsize=15,ytickfontsize=15,legendfontsize=10,
